0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 22, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104lcl1665702797930.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lcl1665702797930.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lcl1665702797930.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"lcl1665702797930\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                          \n Field Interface Library \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Use this editor to model reusable values for the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Database\n      Interface</span> property of fields, which defines the field's physical characteristics\n    when stored. </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lcl1665702797930__p_d7403e1_d7404e1_d7405e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yyf1665702556802.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yyf1665702556802.html\" title=\"This property (also known as the field interface) determines how data in the field is physically stored in the database.\">Database Interface (Fields)</a>.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lcl1665702797930__section_qjx_q4g_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d744242e71\">Properties</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"lcl1665702797930__ul_xqb_r4g_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcl1665702797930__li_d3617e1_d3618e1_d3619e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jrq1665702585385.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jrq1665702585385.html\" title=\"Name of the development object, which uniquely identifies it.\">Name</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcl1665702797930__li_d3620e1_d3621e1_d3622e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xrw1665702585620.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xrw1665702585620.html\" title=\"Use this property to briefly describe the development object in up to 256 Unicode characters.\">Description</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcl1665702797930__li_d3623e1_d3624e1_d3625e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mqg1665702817131.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mqg1665702817131.html\" title=\"Displays the field interface code defined for the template. This is a read-only field.\">Shorthand</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcl1665702797930__li_d3626e1_d3627e1_d3628e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vzh1665702711081.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vzh1665702711081.html\" title=\"Data packing code for the field.\">Data Packing</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcl1665702797930__li_d3629e1_d3630e1_d3631e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vcl1665702711151.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vcl1665702711151.html\" title=\"Physical length of the field in the database, in characters.\">Fixed Length of Field</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcl1665702797930__li_d3632e1_d3633e1_d3634e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nkv1665702792163.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nkv1665702792163.html\" title=\"Data type of the selected parameter. The default value is String.\">Data Type</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lcl1665702797930__p_d7409e1_d7410e1_d7411e1\">It is also possible to define sub-field definitions,\n        variable-length techniques, and use of I/O translation tables. Normally, you do not need to\n        consider these definitions. They are intended only for existing databases that support these\n        features.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lcl1665702797930__p_d7412e1_d7413e1_d7414e1\">Subfield properties (click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">More</span>):</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"lcl1665702797930__ul_crb_r4g_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcl1665702797930__li_d3635e1_d3636e1_d3637e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rwl1665702711264.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rwl1665702711264.html\" title=\"The length of fixed-length subfields in characters, excluding separators.\">Fixed Length of Subfield</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcl1665702797930__li_d3638e1_d3639e1_d3640e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cjw1665702711335.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cjw1665702711335.html\" title=\"Character to be used as the separator between subfields.\">Subfield Separator</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcl1665702797930__li_d3641e1_d3642e1_d3643e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vtx1665702711411.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vtx1665702711411.html\" title=\"The method used to identify the beginning of a subfield.\">Identification Type</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcl1665702797930__li_d3644e1_d3645e1_d3646e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lsl1665702711481.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lsl1665702711481.html\" title=\"ASCII string that marks a variable-length field.\">Field Identifier</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcl1665702797930__li_d3647e1_d3648e1_d3649e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"chv1665702711551.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/chv1665702711551.html\" title=\"ASCII string that marks the first subfield when using variable-length techniques.\">First Subfield Identifier</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lcl1665702797930__li_d3650e1_d3651e1_d3652e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lvh1665702711625.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lvh1665702711625.html\" title=\"Indicates whether data strings should be translated on database input and output.\">Database I/O Translation</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lcl1665702797930__section_ztn_s4g_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d744242e202\">How to</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lcl1665702797930__p_d7784e1_d7785e1_d7786e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lhc1704371292385.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lhc1704371292385.html\" title=\"Create modeled properties using editors available on the More Editors menu. Use a modeled property by clicking the More icon ( icon ) in the appropriate property of an entity or field.\">Working with Modeled Properties</a>\n</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/enu1665702584272.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Database Interface (Entities)</a><p>This property (also known as the entity interface) determines how the data is mapped to the database.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yzg1665702711012.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Modeled Field Interface</a><p>A Modeled Field Interface is a Development Object that defines a reusable value for the Database Interface property of a Database Field.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529496\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529496\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Field Interface Library Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 22, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Field Interface Library Use this editor to model reusable values for the Database Interface property of fields, which defines the field's physical characteristics when stored. For more information, see Database Interface (Fields) . Properties Name Description Shorthand Data Packing Fixed Length of Field Data Type It is also possible to define sub-field definitions, variable-length techniques, and use of I/O translation tables. Normally, you do not need to consider these definitions. They are intended only for existing databases that support these features. Subfield properties (click More ): Fixed Length of Subfield Subfield Separator Identification Type Field Identifier First Subfield Identifier Database I/O Translation How to Working with Modeled Properties Related Links Database Interface (Entities) This property (also known as the entity interface) determines how the data is mapped to the database. Modeled Field Interface A Modeled Field Interface is a Development Object that defines a reusable value for the Database Interface property of a Database Field. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}